    "bbox": [
      210.65,
      450.29,
      401.18,
      462.29
    ],
    "text": "Issued at 05.30 a.m. on 11 May 2026.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 0,
    "bbox": [
      58.56,
      474.65,
      550.3,
      523.99
    ],
    "text": "The low-level atmospheric disturbance in the vicinity of Sri Lanka is likely to develop into a low-pressure area around the next 36 hours. Therefore, the prevailing showery conditions over the island are expected to continue during the next few days.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      0.9599999785423279,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 0,
    "bbox": [
      58.56,
      527.89,
      550.54,
      567.55
    ],
    "text": "Showers or thundershowers will occur at times in most parts of the island and Cloudy skies are expected, under the influence of the aforementioned system.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri",
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      6.960000038146973,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 0,
    "bbox": [
      58.56,
      571.72,
      550.6,
      932.52
    ],
    "text": "Heavy falls about 100 mm are likely at some places in Western, Sabaragamuwa, Central, Uva, Southern, North-western, Northern and North-central provinces and in Trincomalee district. The general public is kindly requested to take adequate precautions to minimize damage caused by temporary localized strong winds and lightning during thundershowers.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri",
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      9.0,
      11.039999961853027,
      12.0
    ]
